# pxx.skip — FPC-testsuite conformance skip list (rung 1, feature-pascal-corpus-fpc-testsuite)
# One test per line: name.pp<TAB>reason. Burn down ticket by ticket; anything
# not passing, not auto-gated, and not listed here = FAIL.
#
# TAXONOMY (feature-testmgr-fpc-compare-and-web-dashboard): the reason MAY lead
# with a tag that the conformance dashboard groups by —
#   gap: <reason>      a real unimplemented pxx feature — open work, burn it down.
#   wontfix: <reason>  the test probes FPC-internal behaviour or something we
#                      intentionally diverge on (RTTI layout, FPC-specific units,
#                      internal-error messages) — it can NEVER pass by design and
#                      is excluded from the adjusted pass rate.
# An untagged reason reads as "untriaged" (the historical entries below). Filling
# these tags is deliberate per-test review (agentic pass, own follow-up ticket);
# add a tag when you've actually decided which bucket a test belongs in.
# Two conventions ride on those tags (triage 2026-07-11, see
# bug-pascal-missing-diagnostics-fail-tests):
#   wontfix: dialect-pass — ...   PXX deliberately accepts what a {%FAIL} test
#       rejects (lax by design, or the test encodes an FPC implementation
#       limit). NOT a bug; do not burn. Future FPC-strict-mode candidates
#       (meta-dialect-extensions-and-fpc-strict). The sweep itself already
#       runs --strict-case; these are divergences with no strict flag yet.
#   gap: accepts-invalid — ...    real missing diagnostic; useful reminder
#       test, burn when the cluster's machinery lands (rainy-day).
# Baseline audit 2026-07-10: 222 pass / 294 skip-listed / 34 auto-gated (of 550 curated).
# Re-audit 2026-07-11 (headerless-program fix, suite re-fetched): 213 pass /
# 303 skip-listed / 34 auto-gated. The header fix green-lit 13 formerly
# failing tests and un-blocked 111 header-required skips (15 pass outright,
# rest re-listed with their real first error); it also EXPOSED 24 {%FAIL}
# negative tests that pxx now compiles instead of rejecting — those were
# previously "passing" only because the mandatory-header error rejected them
# for the wrong reason (see bug-pascal-missing-diagnostics-fail-tests).
# Re-audit 2026-07-11b (case-of-string lowering + case-label validation,
# bug-case-of-string-segfault-and-label-validation): 238 pass / 278
# skip-listed / 34 auto-gated. Burned the tcase cluster (21 entries incl. all
# exit=139 segfaults + the {%FAIL} label-validation tests); the 26 tcase
# sources, enum parsing, or the `otherwise` clause — not on case handling.
